The paper deals with the classification of daily activities from egocentric photo-streams using convolutional and recurrent neural networks. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) since the approach involves training neural networks. The paper also mentions health applications, such as tele-rehabilitation services, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the use of wearable cameras and photo-streams suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
